# Alembic Migrations

This directory contains database migrations for MCPHub using Alembic.

## Creating a New Migration

### Auto-generate from model changes
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "your message here"
```

### Create empty migration
```bash
alembic revision -m "your message here"
```

## Running Migrations

### Upgrade to latest
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Upgrade one version
```bash
alembic upgrade +1
```

### Downgrade one version
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

## Check Current Version

```bash
alembic current
```

## View Migration History

```bash
alembic history
```

## Docker Usage

When running in Docker, ensure the database is ready before migrations:

```bash
docker-compose exec mcp-gateway alembic upgrade head
```

## Notes

- Always review auto-generated migrations before applying
- Test migrations with upgrade/downgrade cycles
- Never modify existing migrations that have been applied to production
- Use descriptive migration messages
